&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I&lt;/strong&gt;nvoices: Review, process, code and verify the accuracy of invoices in a timely manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vendor management: Maintain positive relationships, ensure entirety of vendor profiles in AP systems, and resolve discrepancies promptly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with month end close&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ad hoc projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in accounting, finance, or a related field from a reputed university. Example B.Com or M.Com&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience in accounts payable - 3-5 years experience in AP working for a software services or products company will be an added advantage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with accounting software such as Tipalti, Bill.com, Tallie is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent attention to detail and accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently and as part of a team across multiple time zones.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Excel and Google Worksheets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Candidates should be comfortable working in the 4:00 PM to 1:00 AM IST shift for this role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Life at TripleLift&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
